comments: Finney-Smith (DAL) places his off-arm against Beasley (MIN) during his shot attempt and the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to contest.
Beasley (MIN) does not go through Brunson's (DAL) space and dislodge him from his screening position as Brunson attempts to draw the foul.
Beasley (MIN) reaches in and as he retracts his arm, makes marginal contact with Brunson (DAL) that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) reaches in and makes contact to Towns' (MIN) face at the start of his drive that affects his SQBR.
Finney-Smith (DAL) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Brown (DAL) is positioned sideways and legally contests Towns' (MIN) driving shot attempt.  The marginal contact is created by Towns extending his leg.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Beasley's (MIN) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) makes contact with Russell's (MIN) arm during his rip-through that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Vanderbilt's (MIN) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
Brunson (DAL) extends his arm and makes contact with Beverley's (MIN) face during his drive that affects his ability to defend.
Finney-Smith (DAL) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Towns (MIN) is already in Finney-Smith's (MIN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Russell (MIN) briefly grasps Kleber's (DAL) leg during his drive and immediately slides his hand off.
McDaniels (MIN) makes marginal contact with Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Brown (DAL) makes marginal contact with Towns' (MIN) and disengages as they pursue the loose ball.
Brunson (DAL) makes contact with Beasley's (MIN) arm during his drive that affects his SQBR.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) briefly places his hand to Beverley's (MIN) shoulder and disengages as he gathers the loose ball.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) is in a legal guarding position along the sideline when Beverley (MIN) attempts to drive through and the contact is marginal.
